      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(auto-reply): add memory flush failure tracking with escalation to force-truncate",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFix memory flush failure permanently wedging sessions by adding independent failure tracking with bounded retry and provider-independent force-truncate escalation.\n\nWhen session tokens exceed the `memoryFlush` threshold, OpenClaw spawns an embedded agent turn to produce a handoff summary before truncating history. If this provider call fails (connection closed, 5xx, timeout), the catch block previously only logged and showed a warning — no state was persisted. Since `hasAlreadyFlushedForCurrentCompaction()` still returned `false`, every subsequent message re-triggered the same doomed flush, creating an infinite loop where no user message was ever answered.\n\n## Changes\n\n### `src/config/sessions/types.ts` (+6 lines)\n\nNew optional `SessionEntry` fields for independent failure tracking:\n- `memoryFlushFailureCount` — consecutive failures since last successful flush\n- `memoryFlushLastFailedAt` — timestamp of last failed attempt\n- `memoryFlushLastFailureError` — truncated error message (max 200 chars)\n\n### `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-memory.ts` (+229/-2 lines)\n\n**Failure tracking (catch block, line ~1491):**\n- Non-abort failures: increment `memoryFlushFailureCount`, persist timestamp and truncated error\n- Abort errors (user cancel, gateway restart): no failure metadata persisted, flush retries next message\n- Lifecycle event emitted: `memory_flush_failed` with attempt count and error\n\n**Force-truncate escalation (3 consecutive failures):**\n- Provider-independent: mechanically truncates JSONL transcript to last 20 messages\n- Prepends system marker: `[Session context was automatically truncated due to repeated memory flush failures...]`\n- Resets all failure counters and token estimates\n- Uses `writeTextAtomic` for safe file replacement\n- Lifecycle event emitted: `memory_flush_force_truncate`\n- Visible warning sent to user\n\n**Success path cleanup (line ~1473):**\n- Successful flushes now clear all failure tracking fields\n\n### `src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-memory.test.ts` (+211 lines)\n\nFive new test cases:\n1. `increments memoryFlushFailureCount on non-abort flush failure` — verifies counter, timestamp, error, and lifecycle event\n2. `does not track failure on abort error` — verifies abort exclusion\n3. `clears failure counters on successful flush` — verifies success resets all failure metadata\n4. `triggers force-truncate after MAX_FLUSH_FAILURES consecutive failures` — verifies transcript truncation, marker insertion, counter reset, and lifecycle event\n5. `next message retries flush after failure` — verifies no retry suppression (unlike v1 approach)\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: memoryFlush failure permanently wedges sessions in an infinite flush→fail→flush retry loop, with no escalation path (Issue #85645)\n- **Real environment tested**: Docker container (`node:24-bookworm`, Node.js `v24.16.0`, Linux `aarch64`), local patched checkout at commit `74385e7d`\n- **Failing proof before fix**: On `upstream/main` (commit `827ceb55`), the catch block has zero state persistence and zero escalation. The five test cases authored in this PR do not exist on upstream/main:\n\n```\n# upstream/main catch block — no failure tracking, no escalation:\n  } catch (err) {\n    logVerbose(`memory flush run failed: ${String(err)}`);\n    const visibleErrorPayload = buildMemoryFlushErrorPayload(err);\n    if (visibleErrorPayload) {\n      params.onVisibleErrorPayloads?.([visibleErrorPayload]);\n    }\n  }\n```\n\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\n```bash\n# Docker build\ndocker build -t openclaw-test -f Dockerfile.test .\n\n# Target tests (39 tests, 5 new)\ndocker run --rm openclaw-test\n\n# Regression tests (40 tests)\ndocker run --rm openclaw-test node scripts/run-vitest.mjs \\\n  src/auto-reply/reply/reply-state.test.ts\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n\n```\n# Target tests:\n ✓  auto-reply  src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-memory.test.ts (39 tests) 1120ms\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  39 passed (39)\n\n# Regression tests:\n ✓  auto-reply  src/auto-reply/reply/reply-state.test.ts (40 tests) 31ms\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  40 passed (40)\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**:\n  - Failure path: catch block increments `memoryFlushFailureCount` (independent of success marker), emits `memory_flush_failed` lifecycle event, and does NOT suppress retry on next message\n  - Escalation path: after 3 consecutive failures, `forceTruncateSession()` mechanically truncates the JSONL to last 20 messages + system marker, resets all counters, emits `memory_flush_force_truncate` lifecycle event — no LLM required\n  - Recovery path: successful flush after transient failure clears all failure metadata\n  - Force-truncate test verifies: 25 messages → truncated to 20 + marker (22 lines total), old messages dropped, counters reset\n\n- **What was not tested**: Live end-to-end provider crash with a real OpenClaw Gateway instance. The force-truncate path is tested against real JSONL files on disk but with mocked `runWithModelFallback` rejection. Live provider crash would require a provider that crashes on demand.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-memory.test.ts` — 39 tests passed (Docker + local)\n- [x] `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/reply-state.test.ts` — 40 tests passed (Docker + local)\n- [x] `git diff --check` — no whitespace issues\n- [x] No AI markers in commit, code, or comments\n\nPartially addresses #85645 (implements failure tracking, bounded retry, and provider-independent force-truncate escalation; configurable escalation policy is out of scope for this PR)\n",
